Serves: 4Ingredients:30ml (2 tbsp) olive oil1 onion, finely chopped2 garlic cloves, crushed1 x 400g can Italian chopped tomatoesPinch of sugar or xylitolSalt and black pepper to taste600g prawns, cleanedHandful fresh parsley or dill, chopped100g feta cheese, cubedMethod:1) Preheat the oven to 180 C.2) Heat the oil in a large pan and fry the onion until soft. Add the garlic and cook over low heat for a minute. Add the tomatoes and bring to the boil. Reduce heat and simmer gently for 15 minutes or until mixture thickens.3) Stir in sugar and season, then stir in the prawns and parsley or dill. Pour into an ovenproof dish, add the feta and bake for 10-15 minutes. Don't overcook the prawns. Serve hot with rice. This is one of many tasty recipes you'll find in the new 'Sunday Times Food Weekly Cookbook 4'. It's available at Exclusive Books, Wordsworth and Bargain Books for R179.95.